Not quite. That is a good first test, but it only proves:

python3 -m compileall src

Syntax/imports are okay.

aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode pxe --show
aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode controller --show
aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode full --show

The display path works and --show respects --mode.

It does not prove the saved config, generated vars, status, or deploy gating are correct.

I’d run this next:

aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode pxe
aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode controller
aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode full

Then test the important bug we fixed: controller mode should turn NFS back on by default when --mode controller is supplied.

aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode controller \
  --interface ens160 \
  --server-ip 192.168.109.10 \
  --network 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --gateway none \
  --nfs-export-path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle \
  --nfs-allow-clients 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --target-mount-path /home/unix/sysadmin

Expected:

PXE Server:
  Enabled                        : no
Ansible Controller / NFS:
  Enabled                        : yes
  NFS enabled                    : yes
Firewall intent:
  Services                       : nfs, mountd, rpc-bind
  Ports                          : none

Also test the explicit override:

aerolitctl configure server --dry-run --mode controller --no-nfs \
  --interface ens160 \
  --server-ip 192.168.109.10 \
  --network 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --gateway none \
  --nfs-export-path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle \
  --nfs-allow-clients 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --target-mount-path /home/unix/sysadmin

Expected:

Ansible Controller / NFS:
  Enabled                        : yes
  NFS enabled                    : no

Then, to prove deploy behaves right, you need to actually save each mode and run deploy dry-run.

PXE mode:

aerolitctl configure server \
  --mode pxe \
  --interface ens160 \
  --server-ip 192.168.109.10 \
  --network 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --dhcp-start 192.168.109.100 \
  --dhcp-end 192.168.109.149 \
  --gateway none \
  --nfs-export-path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle \
  --nfs-allow-clients 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --target-mount-path /home/unix/sysadmin
aerolitctl status
aerolitctl deploy server --dry-run

Expected: PXE playbook runs, controller playbook skipped, NFS/controller skipped.

Controller mode:

aerolitctl configure server \
  --mode controller \
  --interface ens160 \
  --server-ip 192.168.109.10 \
  --network 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --gateway none \
  --nfs-export-path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle \
  --nfs-allow-clients 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --target-mount-path /home/unix/sysadmin
aerolitctl status
aerolitctl deploy server --dry-run

Expected: PXE playbook skipped, Ansible controller playbook runs, NFS/firewall services are included.

Full mode:

aerolitctl configure server \
  --mode full \
  --interface ens160 \
  --server-ip 192.168.109.10 \
  --network 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --dhcp-start 192.168.109.100 \
  --dhcp-end 192.168.109.149 \
  --gateway none \
  --nfs-export-path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle \
  --nfs-allow-clients 192.168.109.0/24 \
  --target-mount-path /home/unix/sysadmin
aerolitctl status
aerolitctl deploy server --dry-run

Expected: PXE and Ansible Controller / NFS both enabled.

Finally check the generated vars:

grep -E "aerolit_pxe_enabled|aerolit_controller_enabled|aerolit_nfs_enabled|aerolit_server_mode" \
  /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_server_generated.yml

So: your three commands are enough for a quick smoke test, but not enough to say everything is fixed. The save + status + deploy dry-run tests are what prove the actual behavior.